snort.cleanlogs and  suricata.cleanlogs will take care
to clean up the unified log files in the snort and suricata
logging directory.

Installation.

cp snort.cleanlogs /etc/cron.daily/

cp suricata.cleanlogs /etc/cron.daily/

chmod ugo+x /etc/cron.daily/snort.cleanlogs

chmod ugo+x /etc/cron.daily/suricata.cleanlogs

Configuration.

At the beginning of each script there's a DAYS variable.

#Specify how many days to keep the Unified2 logs before deleting.
DAYS=5

